reasonable if they_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Are comparable to costs incurred for similar services furnished by similar physicians and other suppliers in
the same or a similar location; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Do not exceed what HCFA would pay, in the aggregate (as determined under subpart E of part 405 or part 415 of this
chapter, as appropriate), for the same services under the fee-for service system. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) An HCPP must use the Medicare billing codes to document, on its cost reports, the cost of each part B service furnished
to its Medicare enrollees. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
